If a boat is tipped a small amount, the weight of the boat and the effect of 
buoyancy act to right the boat, see Figure~\ref{fig:buoyancy}. 
However, there is an angle where, if the boat is tipped past that angle, the forces 
will act in the opposite way -- to suddenly and catastrophically flip the boat.
A \emph{tipping point} is where the behavior of a system fundamentally changes. 
There is concern that Earth's ecosystem services may have reached or are near a tipping
point, that is, they have been disturbed to the point of being on the edge of 
catastrophic collapse.

