The limit for atmospheric carbon dioxide concentration
is no more than 350 ppm (current value is more than 412 ppm, see Figure~\ref{fig:CO2Graph}).
Less than 15\% of Earth's land area should be converted to cropland (currently 11.7\% is cropland).
The extinction rate should be less than 10 species per million species becoming extinct
per year. 
Currently, the rate is more than 100 per million, out of a total of 10 to 14 million
species, see Chapter \ref{chap:population}, and is accelerating. 
Generating new species by natural evolution to replace the ones that have been 
lost will take several million years \cite{Davis11262}.

