CO$_2$ is an especially important sustainability issue because of its widespread 
effects. 
It is also especially important for at least two other reasons. 
First, it may trigger a tipping point or points in the Earth's ecosystems, for instance,
related to deforestation, wild fires, ocean acidification, and species loss. 
Second, CO$_2$ is a variable humans can control. 
Anthropogenic CO$_2$ emissions are primarily related to human energy use.

